INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L051$$, 2026, $$Commercial Cargo Vehicles (CCV) - The Commercial Cargo Vehicles program is a centrally managed program for procurement of commercially available and general-purpose vehicles such as heavy and light
 trucks, special purpose trucks, certain fire department trucks, refuse collection trucks, tanker trucks, and all types of trailers.

 Emergency Response Vehicles (ERV) - The Emergency Response Vehicles (ERV) program is a centrally managed, Garrison Mobile Equipment (GME) initiative focused on procuring fire apparatus (e.g., fire
 engines, ladder trucks, rescue vehicles, ambulance, water tankers, and wildland fire apparatus) to ensure installation resiliency before, during, and after man-made, natural, and wartime emergencies. The
 program identifies and addresses vehicles that have reached the end of their life cycle, requiring recapitalization or modernization to mitigate rising sustainment and maintenance costs, ultimately protecting
 Marines, families, civilians, and USMC Missions in both peacetime and wartime.
 Marine Corps Embassy Security Group - Funds the procurement of commercial vehicles for the Marine Security Guards based on the requirements of the command and country embassies.

 Garrison Transportation and Management - The Garrison Transportation and Management program is a centrally managed program that procures commercially available, general purpose, and passenger
 vehicles such as heavy and light trucks, special purpose trucks, certain fire department trucks, refuse collection trucks, tanker trucks, and various types of trailers, as well as sedans, vans, and buses of varying
 sizes. Additionally, the program supports Defense Policy Review Initiative (DPRI) requirements.

 [P40A / Emergency Response Vehicles]: The $2.608M increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is the budgeted cost for DPRI being added in FY27. This funding supports DPRI Okinawa Camp Schwab.

 [P40A / Garrison Transportation and Management]: The increase of $1.425M from FY26 to FY27 results from the procurement of additional vehicles to replace aging assets within the garrison vehicle fleet.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
