 Vehicles (FoV) to include the development and testing of Command, Control, Communications, Computers, & Intelligence (C4I) for integration with the JLTV. JLTV is a joint program between the U.S. Army and
 the U.S. Marine Corps, of which the U.S. Army is the procurement lead and primary inventory control authority (PICA) while the Marine Corps is the requirement lead. The JLTV FoV is capable of performing
 multiple mission roles designed to provide protected, sustained, and networked mobility for personnel and payloads across the full Range of Military Operations.

 Army, as the procurement lead, competitively issued the follow-on production award to AM General LLC on 09 Feb 2023 as a single award five-year requirements contract with five one-year options.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
