INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2032_L011$$, 2027, $$The FY 2027 request for Mid-Range Capability (MRC) includes $370,351 thousand of discretionary and $2,331,282 thousand of mandatory for a total of $2,701,633 thousand. The mandatory funds for MRC
 procures a total of 234 Tomahawk missiles and 110 SM-6 missiles to support Munitions Acceleration Council (MAC) expanded production rate.

 This budget line procures Tomahawk and Standard Missile-6 (SM-6) missiles to meet the Army Total Munition Requirement and procures MRC Ground Support Equipment end items and components.

 The Mid-Range Capability is a ground launched, long-range precision fires offensive weapon system to defeat Anti-Access/Area-Denial (A2/AD) threats and other high value targets to enable warfighter
 dominance in support of Long-Range Precision Fires, Multi-Domain Operations, and Joint Force objectives.

 Each battery consists of four launchers equipped with a Vertical Launching System capable of carrying four of the U.S. Navy's Tomahawk and/or SM-6 with a basic load of 16 missiles, one Battery Operations
 Center (BOC) with support vehicles, and a reload capability.

 Tomahawk missiles procured on Navy contracts includes the Block V modernized Tomahawk Land Attack Missile (TLAM) and beginning in FY25, the Army is procuring Block Va Maritime Strike Tomahawks
 (MST).

 SM-6 missiles procured on Navy contracts will be in the Block IA configuration. The MRC SM-6 missiles provide land and naval surface targeting capability. SM-6 missiles are procured as an all up round
 including guidance, ordnance, MK 72 Boosters, and a MK 21 Canister.$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                            Date: April 2026
