 Description:
 The Stinger Block I missile is an advanced, fire-and-forget, short-range, Soldier-portable, shoulder-fired and platform mounted guided missile system that provides the air defense protection for the maneuver
 force and point defense assets. Stinger's mission is to provide the force with low-altitude air defense against Fixed Wing (FW) and Rotary Wing (RW) Aircraft, Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS) and Cruise
 Missiles (CM). The Stinger missile is deployable from a variety of platforms that includes vehicles, helicopters and UAS.
