INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L061$$, 2027, $$The Family of Explosive Ordnance Disposal Equipment (FEODE) provides critical Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) specialized equipment and toolkits. The Littoral Explosive Ordnance Neutralization (LEON)
 System of Systems as well as EOD robotic systems. These assets enable EOD units to detect, locate, access, identify, triage, diagnose, stabilize, render safe, neutralize, recover, exploit, and dispose of
 unexploded explosive ordnance, improvised explosive devices, and weapons of mass destruction. The FEODE supports Marine Corps EOD operations across the competition continuum and delivers enhanced
 standoff capabilities, increased technician safety, and mission effectiveness. FEODE provides EOD units the required capabilities to counter Explosive Hazards (EH) in support of MAGTF operations, Marine
 Special Operations Forces, and joint missions. They accomplish this by enabling safe operations in littoral regions and on land. The program includes advanced EOD robotics systems, autonomous EOD robotics
 systems, littoral EH detection, littoral EH neutralization systems, radiation detection, radiation identification equipment, personal protective equipment, and render-safe tools.

 The Explosive Hazard Defeat Systems (EHDS) portfolio is the Marine Corps' primary mechanism for ensuring freedom of maneuver in contested maritime terrain. It directly equips the Fleet Marine Force with the
 ground capabilities needed to overcome explosive threats and dominate complex environments.

 This portfolio delivers a modular and scalable toolkits. Integrating crewed, robotic, and autonomous systems allowing them to conduct critical engineer reconnaissance, clear obstacles, and defeat explosive
 hazards. By providing systems that can map terrain and then detect, mark, and neutralize threats, EHDS empowers maneuver forces to operate with confidence in otherwise impassable areas. Ultimately, these
 capabilities enhance force protection, enable decisive maneuver, and provide commanders with the real-time battlespace awareness needed to make faster, more effective decisions.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
