 Description:
 The Family of Construction Equipment Line Item consists of the Family of Material Handling Equipment (FMHE), Family of Construction Equipment (FCE) and Garrison Transportation and Management (GTM).
 The FMHE and FCE programs provide replacement and Service Life Extension Program (SLEP) capabilities for Marine Corps construction and material handling assets. This equipment supports Fleet Marine
 Force construction requirements including littoral transition points, beach preparation, airfield development, combat trails, fuel berms, force protection, counter-mobility obstacles, roads, survivability positions for
 air defense systems, and general engineering support to forward operating bases and lodgment areas.

 The Family of Material Handling Equipment (FMHE) program provides the Marine Corps with a comprehensive suite of platforms including the TRAM, EBFL, APL, and LCRTF that support movement, distribution,
 and sustainment of equipment and materiel across expeditionary and garrison environments. This equipment enhances MAGTF logistics throughput and survivability, introduces autonomous and lightweight
 platforms for distributed operations, replaces obsolescent legacy systems, and supports ship-to-shore, EABO, and prepositioning logistics concepts in contested and degraded environments. The Family of
 Material Handling Equipment (FMHE) include the following systems:

 -The Tractor, Rubber-Tired, Articulated Steering, Multi-Purpose (TRAM) is a diesel-powered, four-wheel drive articulated loader that provides 15,000-pound lifting capacity for earthmoving, excavation, and
 container handling operations at ports, airfields, and construction sites in distributed and austere environments.

 -The Extendable Boom Forklift (EBFL) provides 11,000-pound lifting capacity with an extendable boom for handling ISO containers, pallets, and cargo in confined spaces, and is capable of loading and unloading
 CH-53 helicopters to support rapid airlift operations and forward-positioned forces.

 -The Autonomous Palletized Loader (APL) is an autonomous material handling system with 10,000-pound capacity that can load and unload 463L pallets to/from aircraft such as CH-53, C-130, and C-17 without
 requiring personnel, improving equipment utilization and providing force protection in kinetic environments.

 -The Light Capability Rough Terrain Forklift (LCRTF) is a lightweight, all-terrain forklift designed for operations in tight or degraded environments, providing air-transportable material handling capability for small,
 palletized loads, ammunition, and sustainment materiel to support early-entry forces and littoral logistics operations.




