INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L069$$, 2027, $$The Fuels Support Equipment (FSE) program funds for the procurement of Fuels Operational Readiness Capability Equipment (FORCE). It provides the capability to receive, store, and issue petroleum products
 and support aircraft generation in austere locations where fixed systems do not exist or which require augmentation. This equipment is part of the Air Force's prepositioned war reserve materiel (WRM) and will be
 managed in accordance with 10 U.S.C. 2229, Strategic Policy on Prepositioning of Materiel and Equipment.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount includes $34,794 thousand of discretionary and $29,000 thousand mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $63,794 thousand. Mandatory funds spend plan includes procurement
 of Force Servicing variations (6 of FS, 5 of RC), Aerial Bulk Fuel Delivery Systems/Agile Fueling Systems (20), R19 Fuel Separator Unit (11), R18 Fuel Pumping Assembly (17), R20 Servicing Platform (5), and
 Joint Spoke Refueler (19).

 3K Collapsible Fuel Tanks (CFT) are specifically designed to be loaded on military aircraft and withstand the critical demands put on them during flight operations, in conjunction with the ABFDS they provide the
 ability to transfer fuel from the aircraft storage bladder while aircraft engines are running.
 Aerial Bulk Fuel Delivery System (ABFDS)/Agile Fueling System (AFS): Designed for aerial delivery of fuel to locations where other methods of transportation are impractical. It enables aircraft to rapidly transport
 fuel to locations close to or behind enemy lines and is a key component to the AF Special Operations community and their ability to complete Forward Area Refueling Point missions.

 All-Terrain Berm: Portable secondary containment system designed to be used with large primary fluid storage devices that do not have integral secondary containment capabilities such as Fuel Storage
 Bladders. It protects the surrounding environment from potential liquid spills that may contaminate the soil or water supply. These berms are quickly deployable, structurally supported liner systems providing
 temporary containment in harsh austere/semi-austere locations that do not allow permanent construction, especially in challenging environments.

 Fluid Powered Additive Injector Cart (FPAIC): allows injection of additives (corrosion inhibitor, static dissipater, and fuel system icing inhibitor) into commercial aviation grade fuel to convert it into military grade
 fuel in austere locations.

 FORCE Servicing (FS), Receipt (RC) and Sustainment (SC) is a deployable modular fuel system that can provide joint capability to fuel aircraft and support equipment at forward locations. The FORCE system
 can be configured to perform limited aircraft fueling missions or to sustain massive daily fueling requirements for months. FORCE is capable of receiving, transferring, and issuing fuel at a throughput rate of 900
 Gallons per Minute (GPM). The individual pieces of equipment that comprise the FORCE system provide stand-alone or mix-and-match capability for almost any fuel transfer or aircraft refueling scenario. The full$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
