 Funding in FY 2027 to USAFE will procure 12 interoperable command, control, security operations tactical radio/satellite communications equipment and battlespace/geospatial joint friendly forces tracking
 systems to support mounted (e.g., armored/unarmored tactical vehicles) and dismounted combat and defensive operations; ground and air tactical sensor/ radar systems; electronic countermeasure warfare
 systems; ground & air kinetic/non-kinetic weapons and support equipment in support of Global Force Management/AFFORGEN and ACE constructs. "Fiscal Year (FY) 2025 European Deterrence Initiative (EDI)
 funding accounted for in the Base budget total 30.794M and supports Air Base Ground Defense USAFE programs

 Funding in FY 2026 for Security Force Command and Control (C2) Equipment will be used to procure 1 Base Defense Operations Center (See LOGDET requirement), to include communications equipment, to
 support security forces deployed OCONUS.

 Air Base Ground Defense received a Congressional add for FY2026 32.000 million for "Program Increase, NASAMS" in support of AFRICOM UPL. Upon Congressional spend plan approval, an Internal
 Reprogramming (IR) will be processed aligning the funding to PE0207522F for proper execution.

 PE 0207589F BASE PHYSICAL SECURITY SYSTEMS [BPSS]
 Funding in FY 2027 for Integrated Base Defense Security System (IBDSS-4) will support force protection installs of Weapons Generation Facilities (WGFs), and non-nuclear (PL-1,2,3,4) assets (weapon systems,
 aircraft, command & control systems, etc.) and facilities (hangars, SCIFs, etc.) at AF, USSF and installations globally and Interim Contractor Support at AF and USSF bases. IBDSS systems will be cloud enabled
 and integrated to a common operating picture by integrating electronic security systems with Physical Security Information Managers (PSIM). Due to world-wide operational mission events, quantities are subject
 to change. IBDSS-4 will procure Tactical Security Systems (TSS) and other tactical/expeditionary equipment that is required to provide robust force protection capabilities worldwide. FY2027 procurement
 features fourteen (14) IBDSS-4 modernization installs, ten (10) Physical Security Information Managers (PSIM), and eighteen (18) TSS.

 PE 0208047 ANTITERRORRORISM [AT].
 Funding in FY 2027 regarding BPAC 834130 Electronic Security Systems (ESS) will procure a Containerized Weapons System and 3 (three) Joint Light Tactical Vehicles for the AFAFRICA mission.

 PE 0205671 Joint Counter Remote Control Improvised Explosive Devices (RCIED) Electronic Warfare (JCREW).
 Funding in FY27 will fund Navy-led, joint Navy/AF program to replace legacy quick reaction capability CREW systems that cannot defeat advanced RCIED threats. I1B1 is the new fielded system that is a multi-
 mission capable system that defeats RCIED (explosive devices) and UAS (drones) threats.

 Efforts with funding starting in FY 2025 through FY 2028 are summarized on the P-40.

 The following cost deltas reflect funding for all 834130 Budget Program Activity Code (BPAC) PEs in the years FY26-29 except for PE 0207589F (Base Physical Security Systems). Base Physical Security
 Systems PE uses a P-3a through FY26 because it was categorized as a modification. All other 834130 PEs are not modifications and therefore use P-5s. Base Physical Security Systems PE is transitioning to a
 P-5 exhibit starting in Budget Year (2027) to support identification of end-item deliveries, to include the Tactical Security System (TSS).


 Efforts with funding starting in FY 2028 through FY 2031 are summarized on the P-40. Not all details of this funding are included in this P-40 exhibit set. A summary of the excepted details is as
