INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2035_L037$$, 2026, $$8151B70000 / COE Tactical Server Infrastructure (TSI) base procurement funding in FY 2026 and beyond was realigned to Lines B29810 (Item Number B29801) and BA9301 (Item Number B99418), in support
 of the Army's Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) initiative to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems, Infrastructure Layer. This capability, along with its resources and requirement will
 transition under the overarching NGC2 capability to eliminate stove-piping, reduce duplication of effort, and provide capability within a single NGC2 core architecture.

 The Tactical Server Infrastructure (TSI) is the server hardware platform that hosts Mission Command applications and enterprise software in Army units from the Battalion echelon up through the Army Service
 Component Command. The TSI provides the computing and data storage hardware/software required to host the tactical Computing Environments, supported Warfighter Functional Area applications, Cross-
 Cutting Capabilities and enables the collaborative work environment.

 TSI standardizes server configurations using Commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) hardware and software and TSI provides a common hosting platform for mission command systems. It extends support to the
 migration of future warfighting capabilities and facilitates cloud computing capabilities in the tactical space.$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                           Date: April 2026
